      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">12. Customize request behavior with <code>init()</code> options</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>Most request behavior works well with defaults, but a few options matter for production integration:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>headContentSelectors</code>: controls which <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> elements sync during <code>het-nav</code></li>
          <li><code>replaceContent</code>: swaps DOM with your own replacement strategy, such as morphing instead of replace</li>
          <li><code>nonce</code> and <code>nonceHeader</code>: add a nonce header to enhanced requests</li>
          <li><code>trustedTypesPolicy</code>: transform response HTML before parsing</li>
          <li><code>onError</code>: centralize request and runtime error handling</li>
        </ul>
        <p><code>replaceContent</code> applies to full pane swaps, <code>het-select</code>, and <code>het-also</code> replacements, so use it when you need one consistent replacement strategy everywhere.</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/api#config-options">Config options</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

